IoT-Based Smart Storage System for Enhancing Onion Shelf Life
Project Overview

This project presents an IoT-based smart storage system designed to improve onion preservation and reduce post-harvest losses. The system continuously monitors critical environmental parameters such as temperature, humidity, and spoilage-related gas concentration using DHT11 and MQ135 sensors connected to an ESP32 microcontroller.

The collected sensor data is transmitted to the ThingsBoard cloud platform through Wi-Fi for real-time monitoring, visualization, and historical analysis. When environmental conditions exceed predefined safety thresholds, an automatic ventilation system is activated through a relay-controlled exhaust fan to maintain optimal storage conditions.

