Working Principle

The system continuously collects environmental data from sensors placed inside the onion storage chamber. The ESP32 processes the sensor readings and compares them with predefined threshold values. If excessive humidity, temperature, or harmful gas levels are detected, the relay module automatically activates the exhaust fan to improve ventilation and restore safe storage conditions. All sensor data is simultaneously uploaded to the ThingsBoard cloud platform for remote monitoring and analysis.

